{"word":"λοιδορέω","slug":"λοιδορέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λοιδορέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:λοίδορος'><el>λοίδορος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to abuse, revile</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <i>to rebuke</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to rail at one another</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>λοιδοροῦμαι</el> is also used as <a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <i>to rail at</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>πάντα τὰ αἰσχρὰ λοιδορέονται</el> <i>they use</i> all kind of foul <i>reproaches</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}